<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="739" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/5–1749</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Director of the Office of Far Eastern
                            Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Butterworth</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Director of the
                            Office of Financial and Development Policy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Knapp</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-26">May 26, 1949</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>I concur in the recommendations contained in jour memorandum to me of May 17,
                        1949 with only one reservation. That is, while it may be desirable to
                        withdraw certifications if Chinese funds are being improperly dissipated, I
                        do not believe we should make a firm decision to do so without further
                        consideration of the various implications of such action.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>W. W[<hi rend="smallcaps">alton</hi>] B[<hi rend="smallcaps">utterworth</hi>]</signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>